-- Yield Spread Widens Between 10-Year Bunds and Greek, Irish, Italian Bonds
-- Matthew Brown
-- 2010-06-15T06:50:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/yield-spread-widens-between-10-year-bunds-and-greek-irish-italian-bonds.html

          
          
             Greek 10-year government bond yields
rose relative to those on benchmark German bunds, increasing the
difference by five basis points to 575 basis points as of 7:47
a.m. in London.  
 The so-called yield spread between Irish 10-year bonds and
German bunds widened by 12 basis points to 276 basis points,
while the Italian-German yield widened six basis points to 150
basis points.  
 The Spanish-German spread was little changed at 204 basis
points.  
